Class Relationship

  • java.lang.Object

      • com.github.dkharrat.nexusdata.metamodel.Relationship

  • public class Relationship
extends Property
    A Relationship is a ManagedObject Property that represents a field that stores a to-one or to-many relationship.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Relationship

        public Relationship(Entity<?> entity,
            String name,
            Class<?> type,
            Relationship.Type relationshipType,
            Entity<?> destinationEntity,
            Relationship inverse,
            boolean isRequired)
        Creates a new Attribute.
        Parameters:
        entity - the associated entity
        name - the name of the property
        type - the relationship instance type. For to-one relationships, it must be the same as destinationEntity (i.e. type of the related object. For to-many relationships, it must be Set.
        relationshipType - the relationship type (to-one or to-many)
        destinationEntity - the entity of the object(s) this relationship will store
        inverse - the relationship in the other direction (from the destination entity to this relationship's entity
        isRequired - if true, property is required to have a value
